1
00:01:04,250 --> 00:01:09,421
<i>KELLER: Our Father, who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name.</i>

2
00:01:10,089 --> 00:01:11,924
<i>Thy kingdom come...</i>

3
00:01:12,383 --> 00:01:16,011
<i>...thy will be done,
on earth as it is in heaven.</i>

4
00:01:17,012 --> 00:01:20,057
<i>Give us this day our daily bread...</i>

5
00:01:20,599 --> 00:01:23,269
<i>...and forgive us our trespasses...</i>

6
00:01:23,727 --> 00:01:27,273
<i>...as we forgive those
who trespass against us.</i>

7
00:01:29,066 --> 00:01:31,610
<i>Lead us not into temptation...</i>

8
00:01:32,361 --> 00:01:34,446
<i>...but deliver us from evil.</i>

9
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:40,619
<i>For the kingdom, the power
and the glory are yours...</i>

10
00:01:41,245 --> 00:01:43,163
<i>...now and forever.</i>

11
00:01:44,290 --> 00:01:45,833
<i>Amen.</i>

12
00:01:50,504 --> 00:01:52,548
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

13
00:02:00,764 --> 00:02:03,017
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

14
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:07,605
<i>WEATHERMAN: Looking at mostly cloudy skies
and with lows in the upper 20s...</i>

15
00:02:07,771 --> 00:02:10,316
<i>...there will be some refreeze
on some of the roads...</i>

16
00:02:10,482 --> 00:02:13,277
<i>...so slick spots are possible tonight
in isolated--</i>

17
00:02:15,404 --> 00:02:18,616
You know the most important thing
your granddad ever taught me?

18
00:02:19,491 --> 00:02:20,910
Hmm?

19
00:02:23,621 --> 00:02:25,122
Be ready.

20
00:02:27,499 --> 00:02:32,212
Hurricane, flood,
whatever it ends up being.

21
00:02:32,504 --> 00:02:36,842
No more food gets delivered
to the grocery store, gas stations dry up.

22
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:39,677
People just turn on each other, and, uh...

23
00:02:41,137 --> 00:02:44,849
All of a sudden, all that stands
between you and being dead is you.

24
00:02:50,730 --> 00:02:52,357
I'm proud of you, son.

25
00:02:53,691 --> 00:02:55,276
It was a nice shot.

26
00:03:01,824 --> 00:03:06,871
[GENE MacLELLAN'S "PUT YOUR HAND
IN THE HAND" PLAYING OVER THE RADIO]

27
00:03:07,038 --> 00:03:13,670
<i>Put your hand in the hand of the man
Who stilled the water</i>

28
00:03:14,003 --> 00:03:20,593
<i>Put your hand in the hand of the man
Who calmed the sea</i>

29
00:03:20,927 --> 00:03:24,389
<i>Take a look at yourself
And you can look at others differently</i>

30
00:03:24,555 --> 00:03:27,850
[DOG BARKING]

31
00:03:35,483 --> 00:03:41,614
<i>Every time I look into the holy book
I wanna tremble</i>

32
00:03:51,541 --> 00:03:52,709
GRACE:
Hey, come on, hon.

33
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:54,794
[ANNA HUMMING]

34
00:03:54,961 --> 00:03:57,755
GRACE: Wait. I forgot something.
Hold on a second, Anna!

35
00:03:57,922 --> 00:03:59,799
KELLER: Ralph, you have the venison?
RALPH: Yup.

36
00:04:00,008 --> 00:04:01,592
GRACE:
I forgot the pie.

37
00:04:01,759 --> 00:04:04,846
[ANNA CONTINUES HUMMING]

38
00:04:05,013 --> 00:04:06,097
Are we taking the truck?

39
00:04:06,264 --> 00:04:08,599
We're going up the street, you dope.

40
00:04:11,686 --> 00:04:13,187
Come on.

41
00:04:14,939 --> 00:04:17,233
GRACE:
Hey, wait for your mother, please.

42
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,444
Give me a ride.

43
00:04:21,612 --> 00:04:23,781
KELLER:
Oh, you're getting heavy.

44
00:04:24,449 --> 00:04:27,160
RALPH:
Danny's dad said he'd sell me their old car.

45
00:04:27,326 --> 00:04:29,537
I got half of what I need saved
from the summer.

46
00:04:29,704 --> 00:04:31,205
- I thought maybe--
- Forget it.

47
00:04:31,372 --> 00:04:34,542
I can barely get enough carpentry work
to keep up with the mortgage.

48
00:04:35,376 --> 00:04:38,087
Why don't you rent out Grandpa's
old apartment house?

49
00:04:38,254 --> 00:04:39,464
[GRACE CHUCKLES]

50
00:04:39,630 --> 00:04:43,885
Like I keep telling your mother, it's an old
building. It'll cost a fortune to fix it up.

51
00:04:49,432 --> 00:04:51,309
KELLER:
Oh.

52
00:04:54,644 --> 00:04:56,354
[RALPH COUGHS]

53
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:58,732
[DOORBELL RINGING]

54
00:04:58,899 --> 00:05:00,609
KELLER: Hey.
GRACE: Okay, okay.

55
00:05:00,776 --> 00:05:02,402
NANCY:
They're here!

56
00:05:02,569 --> 00:05:05,155
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING
FROM SPEAKER]

57
00:05:05,322 --> 00:05:07,991
GRACE: Hello.
- Happy Thanksgiving.

58
00:05:08,158 --> 00:05:09,659
KELLER:
Anna, wait until we're invited.

59
00:05:09,826 --> 00:05:11,661
For God's sake, Keller.
Get the hell in here.

60
00:05:11,828 --> 00:05:13,163
[FRANKLIN YELLS THEN GIRLS SCREAMS]

61
00:05:13,330 --> 00:05:14,956
[FRANKLIN LAUGHS]

62
00:05:15,123 --> 00:05:16,875
RALPH: Happy Thanksgiving.
- Happy Turkey Day.

63
00:05:17,042 --> 00:05:19,753
- Keller, got the deer you shot?
- This one's Ralph's.

64
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:22,547
- You killed it, you take it into the kitchen.
- Thank you.

65
00:05:22,714 --> 00:05:25,300
FRANKLIN: I loved that last meal you gave us.
KELLER: There he is.

66
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:27,177
- Thank you. Happy T-Day.
KELLER: How are you?

67
00:05:27,344 --> 00:05:29,387
NANCY: All right.
KELLER: Good to see you.

68
00:05:29,554 --> 00:05:33,642
NANCY: Joy, three times.
Joy, get those dolls off the table.

69
00:05:33,809 --> 00:05:35,977
KELLER: Anna! Anna!
ELIZA: Hi. How are you?

70
00:05:36,144 --> 00:05:37,437
KELLER:
Happy Thanksgiving.

71
00:05:37,604 --> 00:05:39,523
- Hi, Eliza.
- Anna, come here.

72
00:05:40,147 --> 00:05:42,525
We wait until we're invited,
you understand?

73
00:05:42,691 --> 00:05:44,860
NANCY:
You're in charge of this.

74
00:05:45,027 --> 00:05:47,738
Us veterinarians make lousy butchers.

75
00:05:47,905 --> 00:05:49,532
No problem.

76
00:05:52,243 --> 00:05:53,619
ANNA:
Can I go outside with Joy?

77
00:05:53,786 --> 00:05:56,997
Uh, convince your brother
to go with you and you can.

78
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:02,044
And wear a hat, please.
You're just getting over a cold.

79
00:06:02,211 --> 00:06:04,171
Joy, you wear a hat too.

80
00:06:06,340 --> 00:06:08,884
<i>ELIZA:
Did you feel bad for that deer when you shot it?</i>

81
00:06:09,718 --> 00:06:12,805
RALPH: Do you feel bad for cows
when you go to McDonald's?

82
00:06:13,556 --> 00:06:16,684
That's what my dad says.
Deer, if they have too many babies...

83
00:06:16,851 --> 00:06:19,937
...the babies starve anyway.
You gotta keep the population down.

84
00:06:20,104 --> 00:06:21,564
Right.

85
00:06:22,064 --> 00:06:24,358
- Your dad say that too?
JOY: Pull harder.

86
00:06:25,442 --> 00:06:27,361
Hey! Get away from that thing!

87
00:06:27,528 --> 00:06:28,988
Let me see that.

88
00:06:29,155 --> 00:06:31,240
- Come on, let's go.
- No.

89
00:06:31,407 --> 00:06:32,491
RALPH:
I said, let's go!

90
00:06:32,658 --> 00:06:35,327
ELIZA: Stop. Stop. You can't just hit
somebody's stuff like that.

91
00:06:35,494 --> 00:06:38,956
- No! Let's go! Come on, come on.
- Let me--!

92
00:06:39,248 --> 00:06:41,917
Wait. You hear that?

93
00:06:42,710 --> 00:06:44,753
Somebody's in there.

94
00:06:45,045 --> 00:06:48,549
I don't feel like getting yelled at. Let's go.
Don't climb up, okay?

95
00:06:48,716 --> 00:06:50,593
["PUT YOUR HAND IN THE HAND"
CONTINUES PLAYING OVER THE RADIO]

96
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:53,846
[RALPH & ANNA
INDISTINCTLY CHATTERING]

97
00:06:54,013 --> 00:06:58,017
<i>And it causes me shame to know
We're not the people we should be</i>

98
00:07:00,019 --> 00:07:03,355
FRANKLIN: The school board's telling me
there's no money for new band uniforms.

99
00:07:03,522 --> 00:07:06,442
Kids are wearing the same uniforms
they had when we went there.

100
00:07:06,609 --> 00:07:09,445
They were old then.
I mean, marching right out of 1979.

101
00:07:10,529 --> 00:07:12,656
Why isn't he speaking to me?

102
00:07:12,823 --> 00:07:14,658
He doesn't speak.

103
00:07:15,784 --> 00:07:17,620
- Cutie pie.
- Mm-hm.

104
00:07:17,786 --> 00:07:19,413
- Oh, my gosh!
- Whoa.

105
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:21,749
- He's fast too.
- Mm.

106
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:24,418
He's so quick. Is that a slide?

107
00:07:24,585 --> 00:07:27,379
FRANKLIN:
Thank y'all. Thank y'all. Got a surprise.

108
00:07:27,546 --> 00:07:29,381
NANCY:
Oh.

109
00:07:29,590 --> 00:07:32,801
And I am taking requests.

110
00:07:32,968 --> 00:07:34,553
- Yes! Yes.
- No.

111
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,972
[ALL LAUGHING]

112
00:07:37,139 --> 00:07:38,307
Okay.

113
00:07:38,474 --> 00:07:40,893
You gotta listen out for it
because this is not easy.

114
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:43,229
Mommy, can I take Joy to our house?

115
00:07:43,395 --> 00:07:45,189
- Why?
- My red whistle.

116
00:07:45,356 --> 00:07:46,982
She's gonna help me look for it.

117
00:07:47,149 --> 00:07:49,860
Sweetheart, I think that red whistle
is long gone.

118
00:07:50,027 --> 00:07:51,153
NANCY:
What whistle?

119
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:54,573
The emergency whistle Daddy gave me.
I lost it...

120
00:07:56,784 --> 00:07:59,328
...a hundred and 33 days ago.

121
00:07:59,954 --> 00:08:04,166
Well, if you want to find a whistle,
you have to whistle for it.

122
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:06,460
So we'll do "Jingle Bells" to find it.

123
00:08:06,710 --> 00:08:10,089
[FRANKLIN WHISTLING "JINGLE BELLS"]

124
00:08:11,131 --> 00:08:14,593
<i>BOTH [SINGING]: Jingle Bells, Batman smells
Robin laid an egg</i>

125
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:17,346
<i>The Batmobile lost its wheel
And Joker got away</i>

126
00:08:17,513 --> 00:08:18,931
KELLER: Okay.
GRACE: Yay!

127
00:08:19,515 --> 00:08:22,017
Okay! Okay. You can go. All right.

128
00:08:22,184 --> 00:08:25,229
Just make sure Eliza
and Ralph go with you, please.

129
00:08:26,355 --> 00:08:28,107
- No looking in the basement.
- I won't.

130
00:08:28,274 --> 00:08:31,360
Your eardrums are starting to grow.
Don't want to damage them yet.

131
00:08:31,527 --> 00:08:33,988
- But I am taking requests from you, Keller.
- From me?

132
00:08:34,154 --> 00:08:37,199
FRANKLIN: Your day, your request.
- Oh. Uh, the piano.

133
00:08:37,366 --> 00:08:40,035
FRANKLIN: No. So all set?
- No, no, no.

134
00:08:40,202 --> 00:08:43,289
Wait, listen. He used to love--
He used to dress like Springsteen.

135
00:08:43,454 --> 00:08:45,707
KELLER: I still love Springsteen.
GRACE: "Jersey Girl."

136
00:08:45,873 --> 00:08:51,671
Well, I ain't white, and I like him too much,
and I'm too drunk to cover The Boss.

137
00:08:51,838 --> 00:08:53,214
- Thank you.
FRANKLIN: Honey?

138
00:08:53,381 --> 00:08:55,800
GRACE: What else?
- Nothing comes to mind. Nothing.

139
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:57,802
GRACE: Oh, I know.
KELLER: What?

140
00:08:57,969 --> 00:09:02,056
He actually loves "The Star-Spangled Banner."
I know. Sings it in the shower.

141
00:09:02,223 --> 00:09:04,225
- I do not.
- Yes, you do!

142
00:09:04,392 --> 00:09:05,560
FRANKLIN:
I got you.

143
00:09:06,894 --> 00:09:11,399
[PLAYING "THE STAR-SPANGLED
BANNER"]

144
00:09:29,417 --> 00:09:36,424
[CHATTERING ON TV]

145
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:40,928
Where are your sisters?

146
00:09:41,346 --> 00:09:43,097
I can't find them.

147
00:09:43,514 --> 00:09:45,975
You, uh, go to the house with them?

148
00:09:46,142 --> 00:09:47,935
No. What are you talking about?

149
00:09:48,102 --> 00:09:50,438
- Earlier?
- No.

150
00:09:50,605 --> 00:09:54,317
What? They were supposed to come down
earlier and get you. They didn't come?

151
00:09:54,484 --> 00:09:56,277
No. We haven't seen them since we ate.

152
00:09:56,444 --> 00:09:59,113
It's all right. They're probably at our house.

153
00:10:03,951 --> 00:10:07,830
[DOG BARKING]

154
00:10:12,710 --> 00:10:14,128
KELLER:
Anna?

155
00:10:14,295 --> 00:10:16,089
Joy?

156
00:10:17,965 --> 00:10:19,467
Anna?

157
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,220
Girls?

158
00:10:41,739 --> 00:10:42,949
Girls?

159
00:10:43,825 --> 00:10:45,660
- Who put these in here?
- Get out of here.

160
00:10:45,827 --> 00:10:49,414
- They weren't outside. It's starting to rain.
- Did you check by Maria's swing?

161
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:50,998
Yeah.

162
00:10:51,332 --> 00:10:54,794
They're getting whupped when
they get here. Sorry, Grace. I whup kids.

163
00:10:54,961 --> 00:10:56,629
What? So they weren't there either?

164
00:10:56,796 --> 00:10:58,673
- They must be at home.
KELLER: Are they here?

165
00:10:59,006 --> 00:11:01,509
- They weren't there?
- No, they're not at the house.

166
00:11:01,676 --> 00:11:02,718
They're not there.

167
00:11:02,927 --> 00:11:05,471
ELIZA:
I checked the entire house. They're not here.

168
00:11:07,223 --> 00:11:09,225
The RV.

169
00:11:09,392 --> 00:11:12,019
Dad, there was this RV
and they were playing on it.

170
00:11:12,186 --> 00:11:14,605
There was--
We thought there was someone inside.

171
00:11:14,772 --> 00:11:15,982
FRANKLIN: Wait, nobody--
- Where?

172
00:11:16,149 --> 00:11:17,859
Where was it? Show me.

173
00:11:18,025 --> 00:11:19,944
- You wait here.
NANCY: Let me go!

174
00:11:20,111 --> 00:11:22,447
- I'm gonna search the house again.
FRANKLIN: Relax. Relax.

175
00:11:24,615 --> 00:11:27,160
KELLER:
Go that way. I'll meet you on the other side.

176
00:11:28,161 --> 00:11:29,537
Anna?

177
00:11:29,704 --> 00:11:31,247
FRANKLIN:
Joy!

178
00:11:32,373 --> 00:11:34,417
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

179
00:11:34,917 --> 00:11:38,963
- Roger, you seen my daughter walk by here?
- No. ls there a problem?

180
00:11:42,216 --> 00:11:43,759
KELLER:
Anna?

181
00:11:44,051 --> 00:11:47,221
RALPH:
Here! Dad, it was parked right here.

182
00:11:49,389 --> 00:11:52,434
KELLER:
Anna? Anna?

183
00:11:54,478 --> 00:11:56,062
- Hello, hello!
FRANKLIN: Did you see them?

184
00:11:56,229 --> 00:11:58,398
RALPH: No!
- Hello!

185
00:11:59,191 --> 00:12:02,611
- I couldn't find them!
- Were you messing around in this house?

186
00:12:02,777 --> 00:12:04,321
RALPH: No.
- Told you not to come here.

187
00:12:04,488 --> 00:12:06,573
They were on the RV
and we got them off of it.

188
00:12:06,740 --> 00:12:09,075
Tell me everything you remember
about that RV.

189
00:12:09,242 --> 00:12:12,579
- A ladder on the back.
- Police, police.

190
00:12:24,758 --> 00:12:26,676
Happy Thanksgiving.

191
00:12:26,843 --> 00:12:31,181
LOKI: Thanks. Hey, you have any of those
fortune cookie things?

192
00:12:31,347 --> 00:12:34,266
My boss told me cops
don't like fortune cookies.

193
00:12:35,267 --> 00:12:39,104
What year were you born?
Are you a dragon or a snake or a horse, or--?

194
00:12:39,271 --> 00:12:40,773
I'm a monkey.

195
00:12:41,273 --> 00:12:42,566
Oh, you're a monkey.

196
00:12:44,318 --> 00:12:49,448
You're very intelligent.
You have an ability to influence people.

197
00:12:49,615 --> 00:12:52,910
Think you could influence your boss
to lower the check a little bit?

198
00:12:53,077 --> 00:12:57,915
No. I cannot. My boss is a rooster.

199
00:13:03,879 --> 00:13:06,507
So he's selfish and eccentric, that's...

200
00:13:09,802 --> 00:13:12,304
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

201
00:13:12,972 --> 00:13:16,517
<i>DISPATCHER: All units, all units.
An RV was reported matching the description.</i>

202
00:13:16,684 --> 00:13:21,480
<i>The vehicle is parked at a rest stop
off of Route 46, northbound, past exit 17.</i>

203
00:13:21,647 --> 00:13:23,065
<i>Any available units?</i>

204
00:13:23,232 --> 00:13:25,234
<i>POLICEMAN 1 [OVER RADIO]:
This is 12-12 responding.</i>

205
00:13:25,818 --> 00:13:27,486
POLICEMAN 2 [OVER RADIO]:
10-80 responding.

206
00:13:27,653 --> 00:13:31,991
This is 13-40. I'm five minutes out.
I'll meet the responding units.

207
00:13:51,635 --> 00:13:55,014
<i>POLICEMAN 1: 12-12 standing by.
POLICEMAN 2: 10-80 standing by.</i>

208
00:13:55,180 --> 00:13:59,018
13-40. I am on-scene.
Be advised, we are moving in.

209
00:14:35,679 --> 00:14:37,890
[ENGINE REVVING]

210
00:14:39,558 --> 00:14:40,809
LOKI:
Don't move, wait!

211
00:14:40,976 --> 00:14:41,977
Whoa. Whoa!

212
00:14:42,144 --> 00:14:46,065
POLICEMAN 1: Watch out!
LOKI: Hey! Don't shoot! Don't shoot!

213
00:14:48,149 --> 00:14:49,317
Don't shoot!

214
00:14:49,651 --> 00:14:50,735
Don't shoot!

215
00:14:58,493 --> 00:15:00,370
LOKI:
All right, Sloan, take the right!

216
00:15:08,419 --> 00:15:09,962
POLICEMAN 1:
Clear!

217
00:15:15,843 --> 00:15:17,261
POLICEMAN 2:
Clear!

218
00:15:20,139 --> 00:15:22,934
Hey! Wait, wait, wait. I got this.

219
00:15:23,101 --> 00:15:24,811
Give me that.

220
00:15:45,957 --> 00:15:47,250
Hey-

221
00:15:47,417 --> 00:15:50,837
Hey, I see you in there.
Show me both your hands right now.

222
00:15:51,003 --> 00:15:53,631
Hey! I see you in there.
Show me your hands!

223
00:15:56,217 --> 00:15:58,469
Both hands right now!

224
00:15:58,970 --> 00:16:04,308
Nice and slow. Slow. Slow! Slow.
Slowly. Both hands.

225
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:06,811
Both fucking hands!

226
00:16:07,562 --> 00:16:08,980
[GRUNTING]

227
00:16:09,147 --> 00:16:11,607
LOKI:
Walk! Walk!

228
00:16:14,819 --> 00:16:17,572
Walk! Get up! Get up!

229
00:16:19,490 --> 00:16:20,950
Get up!

230
00:16:21,284 --> 00:16:24,370
Show me those girls!
