- Oh.

1201
01:51:16,511 --> 01:51:18,971
My husband kept snakes.

1202
01:51:19,138 --> 01:51:23,518
It wasn't that bad what happened,
but Alex had a fear of them and...

1203
01:51:24,435 --> 01:51:26,646
That's not my favorite memory.

1204
01:51:27,480 --> 01:51:30,400
I'm sorry. It's none of my business.

1205
01:51:30,858 --> 01:51:32,318
Oh.

1206
01:51:35,654 --> 01:51:37,781
Can I get you a cup of tea, Mr. Dover?

1207
01:51:43,745 --> 01:51:44,913
Oh.

1208
01:51:45,080 --> 01:51:48,500
Oh, I'm so sorry. I thought you
would have known about that already.

1209
01:51:49,584 --> 01:51:52,129
I say it's better this way.
You know, that awful man...

1210
01:51:52,295 --> 01:51:57,384
...he would have spent years on Death Row
just watching TV and getting fat.

1211
01:52:01,555 --> 01:52:03,014
Well.

1212
01:52:03,348 --> 01:52:06,685
Least I don't have to worry
about losing you to P.S.P.

1213
01:52:13,191 --> 01:52:18,029
When forensics is finished with the guy's
place, we're gonna deploy the cadaver dogs.

1214
01:52:18,988 --> 01:52:21,740
Look, kid, we can't always save the day.

1215
01:52:22,283 --> 01:52:25,953
All right? We're just cops. Janitors.

1216
01:52:27,580 --> 01:52:29,874
So you lost this one, all right?

1217
01:52:30,040 --> 01:52:32,460
Look, you want fulfillment,
you need to find a girl.

1218
01:52:32,626 --> 01:52:35,045
You know? Start a family, have some kids.

1219
01:52:35,629 --> 01:52:37,339
<i>Let it go.</i>

1220
01:53:57,044 --> 01:53:58,963
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

1221
01:53:59,129 --> 01:54:00,589
Right.

1222
01:54:03,676 --> 01:54:05,719
[CELL PHONE CONTINUES RINGING]

1223
01:54:06,887 --> 01:54:11,058
<i>- Yeah?
RICH: Hey, it's Rich. We found something.</i>

1224
01:54:13,978 --> 01:54:15,980
Guys, let us have a look.

1225
01:54:20,818 --> 01:54:24,488
Two kid-sized department store
mannequins, with their heads caved in.

1226
01:54:24,655 --> 01:54:28,784
I talked to our lab guys. They told me the blood
we sampled from the plastic containers?

1227
01:54:28,951 --> 01:54:30,578
Pig's blood.

1228
01:54:31,412 --> 01:54:35,499
Let's get this covered up.
It's supposed to snow soon. Hurry up, okay?

1229
01:54:38,335 --> 01:54:40,588
It's like he's play-acting.
I mean, case in point:

1230
01:54:40,754 --> 01:54:43,424
Except for the items ID'd
by the Dovers and the Birches...

1231
01:54:43,591 --> 01:54:46,635
...all the kids' clothes that we found
still had tags on them.

1232
01:54:46,802 --> 01:54:49,179
And that maze book that we found,
he made it.

1233
01:54:49,346 --> 01:54:52,016
Photocopies, pictures from this book
we found in the attic.

1234
01:54:52,182 --> 01:54:55,603
- Ex-FBI agent wrote that.
-"Finding the Invisible Man."

1235
01:54:55,769 --> 01:54:59,857
It's about a theoretical suspect he believed
was responsible for a bunch of abductions.

1236
01:55:00,024 --> 01:55:03,694
It's totally discredited,
I guess, but I read some of it.

1237
01:55:03,861 --> 01:55:07,197
Taylor was abducted when he was a kid.
He ran away after three weeks.

1238
01:55:07,364 --> 01:55:10,618
The captor drugged him on some
sort of LSD/Ketamine cocktail.

1239
01:55:10,784 --> 01:55:13,287
He never remembered
and they never caught the guy.

1240
01:55:13,454 --> 01:55:18,292
Okay, so, he read the book and decided
he was taken by the Invisible Man.

1241
01:55:18,459 --> 01:55:21,503
Now he's doing his best imitation, right?

1242
01:55:23,796 --> 01:55:27,675
Yeah, he was doing his best imitation.
He killed himself last night.

1243
01:55:28,635 --> 01:55:30,845
How did he do that?
I thought he was in custody.

1244
01:55:35,642 --> 01:55:37,060
Hey-

1245
01:55:39,062 --> 01:55:41,356
Taylor drew this. It's a map to the bodies.

1246
01:55:41,522 --> 01:55:42,899
It's a map to the bodies.

1247
01:55:43,066 --> 01:55:46,069
We found the same design
on a pendant we pulled off that corpse.

1248
01:55:46,235 --> 01:55:48,404
- There's a connection, okay?
- Connection is...

1249
01:55:48,571 --> 01:55:52,075
...that it's the last maze in the book.
It's unsolvable. There's no way out.

1250
01:55:52,241 --> 01:55:55,828
Your corpse is another wannabe,
read the book.

1251
01:55:56,579 --> 01:55:58,331
What are you saying to me, Rich? What?

1252
01:55:58,498 --> 01:56:00,667
What are you saying, that this guy is a fake?

1253
01:56:00,833 --> 01:56:03,795
You're saying that the girls
are still out there somewhere?

1254
01:56:03,961 --> 01:56:05,880
How did Bob Taylor get those clothes?

1255
01:56:06,047 --> 01:56:08,841
How did--? How did the parents...

1256
01:56:09,008 --> 01:56:11,594
...positively ID those clothes?

1257
01:56:13,596 --> 01:56:15,515
That I can't reconcile.

1258
01:56:15,682 --> 01:56:16,933
You can't reconcile that?

1259
01:56:17,100 --> 01:56:20,228
Just keep knocking on doors,
looking in windows.

1260
01:56:20,520 --> 01:56:22,563
Hey, why is that there? Bag that.

1261
01:56:22,730 --> 01:56:24,899
POLICEMAN 1:
Will do, sir. Right away.

1262
01:57:34,635 --> 01:57:37,096
[PHONE RINGING]

1263
01:57:43,644 --> 01:57:46,773
[PHONE CONTINUES RINGING]

1264
01:57:52,487 --> 01:57:53,946
Yes?

1265
01:57:58,034 --> 01:57:59,494
Yeah, this is she.

1266
01:57:59,660 --> 01:58:02,705
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER THE PHONE]

1267
01:58:03,748 --> 01:58:05,124
What?

1268
01:58:07,460 --> 01:58:09,086
Oh, my God.

1269
01:58:09,253 --> 01:58:12,465
Wait. Is she--?

1270
01:58:13,716 --> 01:58:15,384
Ralph! Keller!

1271
01:58:31,107 --> 01:58:33,485
Keller! We need to go to the hospital!

1272
01:58:33,652 --> 01:58:36,071
They found Joy, but not Anna!
They didn't find Anna!

1273
01:58:36,238 --> 01:58:39,491
Maybe she'll know where Anna is!
Please, we have to go!

1274
01:58:39,658 --> 01:58:41,034
Keller!

1275
01:58:43,912 --> 01:58:46,122
Eliza's not picking up.

1276
01:58:46,289 --> 01:58:48,792
- You should text her.
- Yeah.

1277
01:58:57,801 --> 01:59:00,262
POLICEMAN: Nobody gets beyond this point.
- Don't touch me.

1278
01:59:00,428 --> 01:59:02,889
- Miss! Wait a minute--
- It's okay.

1279
01:59:03,473 --> 01:59:05,267
GRACE: Nancy.
NANCY: Grace.

1280
01:59:05,433 --> 01:59:07,936
They'll find Anna. I know they will.
I know they will.

1281
01:59:08,103 --> 01:59:10,105
GRACE:
I know.

1282
01:59:10,437 --> 01:59:13,190
- How is she?
KELLER: Is she awake?

1283
01:59:14,441 --> 01:59:16,527
Joy, were you far from our street?

1284
01:59:16,694 --> 01:59:19,822
How far from the street were you, Joy? Joy?

1285
01:59:19,989 --> 01:59:22,449
- You can't be doing this.
- How long did it take you to get there?

1286
01:59:22,616 --> 01:59:24,410
- Let me ask a question!
- Keller!

1287
01:59:24,577 --> 01:59:27,454
The detective will be back in just a minute.
You need to wait.

1288
01:59:27,621 --> 01:59:30,416
- She's been drugged.
- Joy.

1289
01:59:30,583 --> 01:59:35,379
Sweetheart, just let us
know she's alive, okay?

1290
01:59:35,796 --> 01:59:39,133
Can you just nod your head, baby?
Just nod your head?

1291
01:59:39,300 --> 01:59:43,804
Baby? Can you give us a nod?
Can you nod your head for us, please?

1292
01:59:43,971 --> 01:59:45,472
Joy?

1293
01:59:56,233 --> 01:59:57,651
KELLER:
Joy.

1294
02:00:27,473 --> 02:00:29,016
[CAR HORN HONKS]

1295
02:00:29,183 --> 02:00:31,060
You were there.

1296
02:00:32,311 --> 02:00:35,272
What? I--? I was where?

1297
02:00:36,982 --> 02:00:40,152
- It put tape on our mouths.
FRANKLIN: Shh.

1298
02:00:41,737 --> 02:00:44,239
It's okay. It's okay, baby.

1299
02:00:45,032 --> 02:00:47,409
It's okay. It's okay.

1300
02:00:47,785 --> 02:00:51,538
Mommy and Daddy are here now,
okay? You're all right.

1301
02:00:51,705 --> 02:00:53,958
- Excuse me.
FRANKLIN: You're all right now.

1302
02:00:54,541 --> 02:00:57,086
I said nobody's allowed in that room
but her family.

1303
02:00:57,252 --> 02:00:59,672
- Hey! Where you going?
- Keller?

1304
02:00:59,838 --> 02:01:02,716
- Hey! Where's he going?
GRACE: I don't know.

1305
02:01:02,967 --> 02:01:05,427
Hey! Call downstairs. Don't let him go.

1306
02:01:05,594 --> 02:01:07,721
Hey! Hey!

1307
02:01:08,222 --> 02:01:09,556
Hey!

1308
02:01:11,600 --> 02:01:13,811
Stop that car! Get his truck!

1309
02:01:13,978 --> 02:01:15,938
Stop it! Hey!

1310
02:01:22,903 --> 02:01:24,905
[CAR HORN HONKS]

1311
02:01:31,160 --> 02:01:33,871
[TIRES SCREECHING]

1312
02:01:38,626 --> 02:01:41,087
I've got you, you fucker.

1313
02:01:41,295 --> 02:01:43,339
I know where you're going.

1314
02:01:44,215 --> 02:01:45,758
I know where you're going.

1315
02:02:09,949 --> 02:02:11,617
[THUDDING NEARBY]

1316
02:02:12,160 --> 02:02:13,870
[ALEX SHOUTING]

1317
02:02:28,801 --> 02:02:30,344
[THUDDING NEARBY]

1318
02:02:34,891 --> 02:02:38,352
[THUDDING THEN ALEX SCREAMING]

1319
02:02:44,150 --> 02:02:45,818
[ALEX SCREAMS]

1320
02:02:56,120 --> 02:02:57,163
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

1321
02:03:04,170 --> 02:03:05,171
Hello again.

1322
02:03:05,671 --> 02:03:10,510
Hey. I was hoping you'd
let me do some penance.

1323
02:03:11,886 --> 02:03:15,932
- For what?
- Scaring you the other day at the, uh...

1324
02:03:16,099 --> 02:03:19,185
- At the police station.
- You already apologized for that.

1325
02:03:19,352 --> 02:03:22,855
I know, I was just--
You know, I thought maybe you, uh...

1326
02:03:23,356 --> 02:03:25,775
You could use some
help around the--

1327
02:03:25,942 --> 02:03:29,529
I noticed your door here needs fixing,
so I brought my tools and, uh...

1328
02:03:29,695 --> 02:03:33,282
Oh. I see.

1329
02:03:35,076 --> 02:03:39,247
I burned myself. Feel a little icky today.

1330
02:03:40,706 --> 02:03:44,085
But I'm glad you want to talk some more.

1331
02:03:44,252 --> 02:03:49,423
No need to make excuses.
You come on in and make me a cup of tea.

1332
02:03:58,766 --> 02:04:00,393
Come on in.

1333
02:04:19,787 --> 02:04:22,165
I don't want to have to hurt you.

1334
02:04:24,542 --> 02:04:26,586
I know they were here.

1335
02:04:28,462 --> 02:04:31,591
Put your hands on your head
and turn around.

1336
02:04:33,133 --> 02:04:34,759
Do it.

1337
02:04:38,013 --> 02:04:39,764
I'm just gonna go.

1338
02:04:39,931 --> 02:04:44,769
Don't touch that bag.
Put your hands on your head.

1339
02:04:49,357 --> 02:04:52,485
Come over here to this counter. Come on.

1340
02:05:01,995 --> 02:05:03,622
Top drawer.

1341
02:05:04,789 --> 02:05:06,124
Open it.

1342
02:05:12,255 --> 02:05:13,924
Mm-hm.

1343
02:05:15,508 --> 02:05:17,219
Put them on.

1344
02:05:27,145 --> 02:05:29,981
You don't know me, Mr. Dover.

1345
02:05:30,232 --> 02:05:34,152
But believe me when I tell you,
I won't let you go.

1346
02:05:42,452 --> 02:05:44,329
You don't have to drink all of it.

1347
02:05:45,538 --> 02:05:48,959
About a third should do for a man your size.

1348
02:05:50,502 --> 02:05:53,463
- Something to make you more manageable.
- Forget it.

1349
02:05:53,630 --> 02:05:58,176
Drink it, Mr. Dover, or I'll kill you right here in
my kitchen and bring your daughter in here...

1350
02:05:58,343 --> 02:06:01,304
- ...and have her scrub your brains off the ﬂoor.
- Where is she?

1351
02:06:02,097 --> 02:06:04,182
[SIGHS]

1352
02:06:04,808 --> 02:06:06,017
Drink.

1353
02:06:06,559 --> 02:06:08,270
Just let me see her.

1354
02:06:08,436 --> 02:06:10,188
- You want to see her?
- Yes.

1355
02:06:10,939 --> 02:06:13,692
That's your ticket
to your daughter right there.

1356
02:06:24,411 --> 02:06:28,081
Little more, Mr. Dover. Little more.

1357
02:06:34,004 --> 02:06:35,797
Good, isn't it?

1358
02:06:36,589 --> 02:06:38,883
That's my darling husband's recipe.

1359
02:06:46,724 --> 02:06:48,392
Now go on out back.

1360
02:06:48,892 --> 02:06:50,811
Let me see her.

1361
02:06:51,103 --> 02:06:52,396
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

1362
02:06:56,233 --> 02:06:58,360
Take it out of your pocket.

1363
02:07:00,738 --> 02:07:02,406
Put it in the sink.

1364
02:07:05,075 --> 02:07:07,077
Put it in the disposal.

1365
02:07:09,246 --> 02:07:10,956
[CELL PHONE CONTINUES RINGING]

1366
02:07:15,419 --> 02:07:17,588
Put your car keys on the table.

1367
02:07:17,755 --> 02:07:20,215
[KELLER SIGHS THEN GROANS]

1368
02:07:20,883 --> 02:07:23,677
Put your car keys on the table.

1369
02:07:25,637 --> 02:07:27,139
That's right.

1370
02:07:27,931 --> 02:07:32,144
Go over to the Trans-Am over there.
The car over there. Come on, move it.

1371
02:07:32,310 --> 02:07:34,103
Get over there.

1372
02:07:41,319 --> 02:07:43,613
The look on your face.

1373
02:07:43,780 --> 02:07:48,618
My husband used to have the very same look
until we took Alex.

1374
02:07:48,785 --> 02:07:50,745
He was the first kid we ever took.

1375
02:07:50,912 --> 02:07:54,624
His name was Jimmy. Or Barry.

1376
02:07:54,791 --> 02:07:57,293
Can't remember. Doubt he can, either.

1377
02:07:57,460 --> 02:07:59,504
So many names.

1378
02:07:59,670 --> 02:08:04,258
Forgot all about Bobby Taylor
until I read about him in the paper.

1379
02:08:06,135 --> 02:08:08,471
Get in the driver's seat.

1380
02:08:17,897 --> 02:08:20,316
Open the door and get in the car.

1381
02:08:35,164 --> 02:08:40,086
Making children disappear
is the war we wage with God.

1382
02:08:41,379 --> 02:08:43,798
Makes people lose their faith.

1383
02:08:43,965 --> 02:08:46,843
Turns them into demons like you.

1384
02:08:48,010 --> 02:08:51,806
Had to slow down
since my husband disappeared.

1385
02:08:51,973 --> 02:08:54,058
But I do what I can.

1386
02:08:55,685 --> 02:08:57,437
Start the car.

1387
02:08:58,104 --> 02:09:00,022
Start the car.

1388
02:09:03,693 --> 02:09:05,403
[ENGINE STALLING]

1389
02:09:05,570 --> 02:09:07,363
Keep trying-

1390
02:09:07,864 --> 02:09:10,366
[ENGINE CHUGS THEN STARTS]

1391
02:09:13,244 --> 02:09:16,038
Back up. Slowly.

1392
02:09:20,042 --> 02:09:23,296
Come on. Back up.

1393
02:09:25,256 --> 02:09:26,716
Come on.

1394
02:09:30,428 --> 02:09:31,888
Stop.

1395
02:09:32,054 --> 02:09:33,556
Turn it off.

1396
02:09:34,348 --> 02:09:36,225
Turn it off!

1397
02:09:37,477 --> 02:09:38,978
Get out.

1398
02:09:48,237 --> 02:09:49,989
Think you should know.

1399
02:09:50,156 --> 02:09:52,575
Alex never laid a hand on those girls.

1400
02:09:52,742 --> 02:09:55,286
Just wanted to take them
for a ride in the camper.

1401
02:09:56,078 --> 02:09:58,748
I was the one who decided
they should stay.

1402
02:10:02,084 --> 02:10:03,753
Take a look.

1403
02:10:05,296 --> 02:10:07,423
Maybe your daughter's under there.

1404
02:10:07,924 --> 02:10:09,675
You never know.

1405
02:10:11,260 --> 02:10:12,720
Anna.

1406
02:10:13,554 --> 02:10:15,056
Anna!

1407
02:10:20,686 --> 02:10:21,771
Anna?

1408
02:10:21,938 --> 02:10:25,441
Anna! Anna! Anna!

1409
02:10:26,275 --> 02:10:30,404
I had the girls down there
while the police came poking around.

1410
02:10:31,239 --> 02:10:32,949
Should have left them down there.

1411
02:10:34,116 --> 02:10:35,785
I was so lonely without Alex.

1412
02:10:38,370 --> 02:10:41,373
- Now get in there.
- What?

1413
02:10:41,873 --> 02:10:43,750
Get in.

1414
02:10:46,962 --> 02:10:49,965
You want me to get in there,
you're gonna have to shoot me.

1415
02:10:50,715 --> 02:10:53,051
I'm not gonna get in there
just because you asked.

1416
02:10:55,136 --> 02:10:56,972
[GROANING]

1417
02:10:57,138 --> 02:10:58,640
God!

1418
02:11:04,145 --> 02:11:07,357
Go on. Get in there.

1419
02:11:09,609 --> 02:11:12,904
[GRUNTING AND GROANING]

1420
02:11:14,656 --> 02:11:16,074
That's right.

1421
02:11:16,658 --> 02:11:19,452
[THUDDING THEN KELLER YELLS]

1422
02:11:28,587 --> 02:11:30,046
[GROANS]

1423
02:11:32,966 --> 02:11:35,135
[GROANING]

1424
02:11:35,844 --> 02:11:38,179
Make yourself a tourniquet.

1425
02:11:38,847 --> 02:11:41,141
Just might last 24 hours.

1426
02:11:46,396 --> 02:11:50,525
I'd love for you to still be alive when I dump
your daughter's body down there.

1427
02:11:51,693 --> 02:11:54,654
[GROANING]

1428
02:11:54,821 --> 02:11:56,448
[BOARD GRATING]

1429
02:11:56,615 --> 02:11:58,700
Wait. No, wait, wait! Wait!

1430
02:12:01,077 --> 02:12:02,579
[BOARD THUMPS]

1431
02:12:04,080 --> 02:12:05,624
KELLER:
Oh.

1432
02:12:26,686 --> 02:12:28,688
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

1433
02:12:28,855 --> 02:12:31,691
Hey. I need you to go over to Holly Jones'.

1434
02:12:31,858 --> 02:12:34,277
- She needs to be notified.
- No. I need to find Dover.

1435
02:12:34,444 --> 02:12:37,656
- Come on. You're done with Dover, okay. Please.
- You want me to go to Holly Jones'?

1436
02:12:37,822 --> 02:12:40,867
I want you to go to Holly Jones'
and notify her, please.

1437
02:12:50,085 --> 02:12:51,544
Pfft.

1438
02:12:55,590 --> 02:12:57,592
[GROANS THEN PANTS]

1439
02:13:02,430 --> 02:13:03,890
[GRUNTS]

1440
02:13:12,357 --> 02:13:13,817
Oh, God.

1441
02:13:32,168 --> 02:13:33,712
[GROANS]

1442
02:14:02,823 --> 02:14:04,450
[SIGHS]

1443
